 header, listed ui-resizable  \"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div class=\"head editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" spellcheck=\"false\"><h4>Lesson Summary</h4></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"4m94f\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list paragraph, listed ui-resizable  \"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"editable p-asset ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><b>The main points from this module are:</b></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li><li id=\"3Cw9t\" data-space=\"\" full-editor=\"\" class=\"component list list-item, listed selected-class   ui-resizable border\"><div class=\"asset-header ng-binding\"></div><div ng-paste=\"removeFormat($event, item.title)\" class=\"list-item editable ng-pristine ng-valid ng-binding ng-scope ng-not-empty None ng-touched\" spellcheck=\"false\"><ul class=\"\"><li class=\"\"><div>The fundamental concept of Islamic finance is that money has\nno intrinsic value and should only be used to measure worth.</div></li><li class=\"\"><div><div>The Islamic economic model has been developed over time,\nbased on the rulings of Shariah on commercial and financial transactions.</div></div></li><li class=\"\"><div>Business ethics examines the ethical principles and rules of commercial and financial institutions.<br></div></li><li class=\"\"><div><div>An Islamic investment fund operates similarly to a mutual\nfund.</div></div></li><li class=\"\"><div><div>Risk is defined as the exposure to unpredictable future\noccurrences that might jeopardise a financial institution’s objectives.</div></div></li><li class=\"\"><div><div>Shariah risk governance policies and guidelines serve as the\nfoundation of an Islamic bank’s risk management strategy.</div></div></li><li class=\"\"><div><div>‘Riba’ means addition, expansion or growth. It is seen as a\nrise in usurious products and debt due to the postponed payment period. It is not allowed in an Islamic financial system.</div></div></li><li class=\"\"><div><div>‘Takaful’ is a process of agreement among a group of persons\nto handle the injuries resulting from specific risks to which all of them are\nvulnerable.</div></div></li><li class=\"\"><div><div>The UK Islamic mortgage market is expected to be 500 million\npounds compared to the stock of mortgage financing of over 1.1 trillion pounds and\napproximately 12 million borrowers.</div></div></li></ul></div><div class=\"caption ng-binding\"></div></li></ul>\n"]}